HEADWORD: Brachyura
<hw>Brach`y*u"ra</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr. <grk>brachy`s</grk> short + <grk>o'yra`</grk> tail.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group of decapod Crustacea, including the
common crabs, characterized by a small and short abdomen, which is bent
up beneath the large cephalo-thorax. <altsp>[Also spelt
<asp>Brachyoura</asp>.]</altsp> See <er>Crab</er>, and
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

